to women. There's a first.

246
00:15:44,544 --> 00:15:47,104
If you're not gonna be
helpful, Claire, just leave.

247
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:52,442
You don't need to
talk. Just listen to her.

248
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:56,412
You get to come out
here, clear your head.

249
00:15:56,489 --> 00:15:59,891
She's trapped in there, alone
with her thoughts, her fears.

250
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:01,439
You don't think she
wants to get out?

251
00:16:02,762 --> 00:16:04,731
You are her escape.

252
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:14,733
You wanna put a fake
femur into Marco's leg?

253
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,332
It's not fake, it's real.

254
00:16:16,509 --> 00:16:19,069
It's not a real bone, we're
making it out of titanium.

255
00:16:19,145 --> 00:16:20,169
It's still real.

256
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:24,113
That's incredible. And Marco
will be able to walk, run, climb?

257
00:16:24,183 --> 00:16:25,310
And swim.

258
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:28,354
Hopefully. That's the intention.

259
00:16:28,788 --> 00:16:31,121
Well, have you done
this surgery before?

260
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:32,818
- I haven't...
- We'll be the first.

261
00:16:35,094 --> 00:16:36,858
Nobody has ever
attempted this surgery

262
00:16:36,963 --> 00:16:38,693
with a bone as
large as the femur.

263
00:16:38,798 --> 00:16:41,290
I believe it's a viable
option, but there are risks.

264
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:44,030
Risks? Could Marco die?

265
00:16:44,136 --> 00:16:45,195
In my estimation,

266
00:16:45,338 --> 00:16:46,815
there's a 10% chance
he won't make it.

267
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:49,274
Then, no. I'm not losing my son.

268
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:52,308
Wait, if there's a chance
we can save Marco's leg,

269
00:16:52,378 --> 00:16:55,041
we should at least discuss this
some more. That's what he'd want.

270
00:16:55,147 --> 00:16:57,673
He'd want to live.
He'd wanna have a life.

271
00:16:58,451 --> 00:17:01,546
I know him. He'd want
to take the chance.

272
00:17:01,654 --> 00:17:03,953
I will never forgive
myself if Marco died

273
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:05,685
because I made a
reckless decision.

274
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:08,856
Whose decision is this?

275
00:17:08,961 --> 00:17:10,293
Does he have a healthcare proxy?

276
00:17:10,663 --> 00:17:11,892
I don't know what that is.

277
00:17:11,998 --> 00:17:15,127
When the accident happened,
were you on the way to your wedding,

278
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:17,670
- or on the way back?
- We were headed to the wedding.

279
00:17:18,905 --> 00:17:21,739
Marco's parents are the
next of kin. They decide.

280
00:17:28,347 --> 00:17:31,909
Please, amputate our son's leg.

281
00:17:37,089 --> 00:17:38,148
Murphy.

282
00:17:45,264 --> 00:17:47,529
Why is the primary
closure on the stump so vital

283
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,727
in amputation surgery?

284
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:53,033
For proper prosthetic fitting.
Why are you marrying Jessica?

285
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:56,339
Why does anyone get married?

286
00:17:57,443 --> 00:17:58,570
I don't know.

287
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:01,675
I love her.

288
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:06,451
I don't understand why having someone
to love is so important to everyone.

289
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:11,685
You have to stand down.
You can't amputate Marco's leg.

290
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:12,781
Why not?

291
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:15,225
I filed an emergency
injunction to stop the surgery.

292
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:22,091
You were in a car accident,
your neck was punctured.

293
00:18:22,902 --> 00:18:25,531
The repair surgery went well.
You're gonna have to stay put

294
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:30,100
for a week before we can release
you. You're very lucky to be alive.

295
00:18:38,384 --> 00:18:42,651
My wife, Jenna
Hensel. Is she okay?

296
00:18:42,922 --> 00:18:43,946
Can I see her?

297
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:52,223
She's not listed.
That's a good thing.

298
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:54,324
She's probably still
in the waiting room.

299
00:18:54,667 --> 00:18:56,158
I'll find her and bring her up.

300
00:18:56,335 --> 00:18:58,167
She'll be relieved
to know you're okay.

301
00:18:59,171 --> 00:19:00,230
Okay.

302
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:03,752
What the hell am I supposed to
do with an unconscious patient

303
00:19:03,776 --> 00:19:05,096
whose leg is a
ticking time-bomb?

304
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,388
Judge Singh is en route.

305
00:19:06,412 --> 00:19:09,177
She wants to hear from both
parties and the doctors on the case.

306
00:19:09,281 --> 00:19:10,579
I have to testify?

307
00:19:10,783 --> 00:19:11,807
Hopefully not.

308
00:19:11,917 --> 00:19:13,476
I thought you would be happy.

309
00:19:13,853 --> 00:19:15,163
You thought you
could save the leg,

310
00:19:15,187 --> 00:19:16,565
and I didn't want
that not happening

311
00:19:16,589 --> 00:19:18,467
because the parents are
afraid to make a tough call.

312
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:19,789
It's their call to make.

313
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:23,023
And if the accident happened an
hour later, it would be the wife's.

314
00:19:23,362 --> 00:19:24,660
And she wants the fake leg.

315
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:25,959
It's not fake.

316
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:29,827
I thought you didn't believe in
just blindly following protocol.

317
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,631
He's their son. Nobody's
gonna love him more than them.

318
00:19:32,772 --> 00:19:36,800
Seriously? All parents love all
children more than anybody else?

319
00:19:36,942 --> 00:19:40,435
People get divorced all the time.
How often do they give up their kids?

320
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,381
So if this was us, you'd want
your parents to decide over me.

321
00:19:43,482 --> 00:19:45,212
- I didn't say that.
- You kind of did.

322
00:19:46,819 --> 00:19:49,015
I was saying there
needs to be rules.

323
00:19:49,555 --> 00:19:51,319
There needs to
be bright red lines

324
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:53,325
telling us who gets
to make these calls.

325
00:19:53,793 --> 00:19:54,886
It's the parents' call.

326
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:57,626
Not anymore. Now it's a judge's.

327
00:19:58,831 --> 00:20:01,043
How much time does Marco
have left on the temporary shunt?

328
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:04,697
Three hours, and
then his leg will die.

329
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:08,864
- Okay.
- Mmm.

330
00:20:18,084 --> 00:20:19,814
Doctor Torture returns.

331
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,650
Thought I'd scared
you off for good.

332
00:20:23,322 --> 00:20:24,346
Pick a movie.

333
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:27,492
You deserve to get out of
this room for a little while, too.

334
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:32,859
You think <i>Groundhog Day's</i>
gonna make a difference?

335
00:20:33,599 --> 00:20:36,899
"I'm torturing you, but, hey,
you get to watch a funny movie."

336
00:20:37,536 --> 00:20:39,528
That is sort of what I
was going for, yeah.

337
00:20:44,043 --> 00:20:45,067
I'm sorry.

338
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,914
I wish there was
something else I could do.

339
00:20:50,549 --> 00:20:51,881
How do you know there isn't?

340
00:20:51,951 --> 00:20:53,852
This is protocol. This
is what they teach...

341
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,114
I lucked out.

342
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:58,448
I got the world's greatest
expert on burn victims?

343
00:20:59,191 --> 00:21:00,955
You know everything
that can be done?

344
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:08,196
He loves to rock-climb,
scuba-dive, bungee-jump.

345
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:13,433
This is insane. His leg is literally
dying while we sit here reminiscing.

346
00:21:13,539 --> 00:21:16,304
Please, we're trying to figure
out what your son would want.

347
00:21:16,408 --> 00:21:18,309
- He'd want to live.
- I want that, too.

348
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:21,403
But if there is a way that
we can save Marco's leg,

349
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:23,074
he'd want me to do it.

350
00:21:23,449 --> 00:21:26,044
<i>Mija,</i> do you know
what he wanted?

351
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:27,142
Most of all?

352
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,446
He wanted to marry you.

353
00:21:31,991 --> 00:21:35,086
He wanted to spend his life
with you, have children with you.

354
00:21:35,161 --> 00:21:38,598
Now, he can do all
that, he can be happy,

355
00:21:39,231 --> 00:21:40,893
with a prosthetic leg.

356
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:43,792
He's young, he's strong.

357
00:21:45,004 --> 00:21:46,802
<i>Mija,</i> he can get through this.

358
00:21:52,278 --> 00:21:53,302
When we met...

359
00:21:53,412 --> 00:21:55,438
I don't care about your stories.

360
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:59,779
I don't care that you
met rock-climbing,

361
00:21:59,852 --> 00:22:02,788
or kayaking, or
whatever. I just want...

362
00:22:02,855 --> 00:22:04,619
We met in rehab.

363
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,625
Hey, are either of
you Jenna Hensel?

364
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:19,831
I haven't seen Jenna since
we took pictures at the hotel.

365
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:21,534
But she got on the bus?

366
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:23,833
Yeah, she was
sitting with Noomi.

367
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:33,516
I think she's still out there.
Hey, guys, we've gotta go back.

368
00:22:33,619 --> 00:22:35,212
- Where?
- To the crash site. Now.

369
00:22:36,555 --> 00:22:38,717
He never wanted you to know.

370
00:22:41,293 --> 00:22:42,522
He's an addict.

371
00:22:42,628 --> 00:22:44,563
He replaced one
addiction for another one,

372
00:22:44,663 --> 00:22:48,156
a healthier one. But he needs...

373
00:22:48,234 --> 00:22:49,293
What?

374
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:52,369
He needs to wakeboard or
he'll drink himself to death?

375
00:22:52,972 --> 00:22:54,031
This is ridiculous.

376
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:57,303
No, it's not. We
talked about it a lot.

377
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:59,402
It's pretty much
all you do in rehab.

378
00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:02,345
Marco has clarity for
the first time in his life.

379
00:23:02,982 --> 00:23:06,043
He knows what makes him
happy. He knows his weaknesses.

380
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:12,518
He's not as strong as you
think. And that's okay, but...

381
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:15,027
Marco cheated on you.

382
00:23:17,997 --> 00:23:19,397
It was about a month ago.

383
00:23:19,999 --> 00:23:22,833
He was overwhelmed with
the wedding and the planning.

384
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:27,028
He ran into an ex-girlfriend.
It only happened once.

385
00:23:29,108 --> 00:23:34,411
You're lying. You're upset that
he had secrets from you, so...

386
00:23:34,513 --> 00:23:36,038
No, she's not lying.

387
00:23:39,618 --> 00:23:42,588
<i>Mija,</i> he was so upset.
He does love you.

388
00:23:42,688 --> 00:23:44,850
Okay, maybe we're
digressing here a little bit

389
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:46,688
and we really don't
have the time...

390
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:48,022
It matters.

391
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:51,426
She doesn't know him like...

392
00:23:53,232 --> 00:23:57,431
Maybe none of us do,
but we are his parents.

393
00:23:58,203 --> 00:24:00,798
And you're not his wife. Yet.

394
00:24:17,589 --> 00:24:19,217
Okay, get the cops,
check everywhere.

395
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:20,953
Other side of the
road, bushes, trees.

396
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:22,203
If she was ejected from the bus,

397
00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:23,923
she could be 40, 50
feet in any direction.

398
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:30,261
Jenna!

399
00:24:33,172 --> 00:24:34,936
I found her. I need some help.

400
00:24:42,514 --> 00:24:45,643
She's got a brain bleed! We
need to get her out of here, now!

401
00:24:49,355 --> 00:24:51,950
Dr. Andrews. I think
Celez may be eligible

402
00:24:52,024 --> 00:24:53,583
for experimental burn treatment.

403
00:24:54,293 --> 00:24:56,353
- Sell it to me.
- I've been doing some digging.

404
00:24:56,462 --> 00:24:59,489
San Diego Community Hospital's
burn unit has been following

405
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:02,625
a Brazilian hospital's protocol
to wrap burns in tilapia skins.

406
00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:05,694
Now... Now, I know fish
skins sound a bit crazy, but...

407
00:25:06,372 --> 00:25:08,372
But I was thinking we
could do the same thing here.

408
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:11,776
Dr. Kalu, I applaud
your thinking, but...

409
00:25:11,844 --> 00:25:15,178
Tilapia skins contain more collagen
proteins, both types one and three,

410
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,374
than even human skin,
which aids in tissue repair,

411
00:25:17,483 --> 00:25:18,960
- negating the need for grafts.
- Dr. Kalu...

412
00:25:18,984 --> 00:25:20,962
It can accelerate healing,
reduce risk of infection,

413
00:25:20,986 --> 00:25:23,012
and cut down on a
patient's physical pain.

414
00:25:23,555 --> 00:25:25,755
Are you finished, or would
you like to cut me off again?

415
00:25:26,658 --> 00:25:29,560
Okay. Let's follow this through,
shall we? You have to come up

416
00:25:29,661 --> 00:25:32,324
with a proposal for the experimental
treatment, get it approved

417
00:25:32,398 --> 00:25:34,799
by our institutional review
board, get your hands

418
00:25:35,067 --> 00:25:37,400
on medical-grade
tilapia skins, and then...

419
00:25:37,503 --> 00:25:39,543
Well, I thought you could
help expedite the process.

420
00:25:42,141 --> 00:25:44,621
You think I could bring it down
from three months to two hours?

421
00:25:46,578 --> 00:25:50,208
You finish the debridement?
Okay. I'll take over from here.

422
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:55,514
Hey. Keep thinking outside
the box. Initiative is good.

423
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:08,561
I'm in. Bag her. Did
you get me the drill?

424
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:10,107
Fire truck had one.
What's going on?

425
00:26:10,202 --> 00:26:12,228
Her pupils are blown. She
has a subdural hematoma

426
00:26:12,337 --> 00:26:14,033
causing increased
intracranial pressure.

427
00:26:14,106 --> 00:26:16,184
If I don't alleviate it now,
there's no way she makes it

428
00:26:16,208 --> 00:26:17,403
to the hospital alive.

429
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:45,863
Unconscious female. Flail chest.
I had to do a burr hole in-field.

430
00:26:46,371 --> 00:26:47,930
Her sats are in the low 70s.

431
00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:58,580
She's good to go to the OR.

432
00:27:00,652 --> 00:27:01,779
Subdural hematoma?

433
00:27:01,887 --> 00:27:04,065
Yeah. She had decerebrate
posturing, a blown left pupil.

434
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:05,733
When I passed the
drill bit through her skull,

435
00:27:05,757 --> 00:27:08,158
- a whole lot of blood pooled out.
- Good call.

436
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:17,300
San Diego Community Hospital
called. They're sending the tilapia skins.

437
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:20,304
They're medevacing 'em in.
Should be here within the hour.

438
00:27:21,273 --> 00:27:25,768
Celez, you meet the criteria
for an experimental treatment

439
00:27:25,844 --> 00:27:28,404
that I think will prevent you
from having to undergo skin grafts.

440
00:27:28,914 --> 00:27:30,974
Hold up. How did
this even happen?

441
00:27:31,083 --> 00:27:34,781
Well, I found out San Diego's trial
allows for multi-site collaborations,

442
00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:38,513
so there's no need for us to get
our own IRB. They give us the skins,

443
00:27:38,690 --> 00:27:39,851
we provide the patient data.

444
00:27:40,125 --> 00:27:41,149
Fish skins?

445
00:27:41,426 --> 00:27:44,191
The tilapia skins have
been cleaned and sterilized,

446
00:27:44,296 --> 00:27:45,821
they're perfectly safe.

447
00:27:49,935 --> 00:27:51,130
You'll do it?

448
00:27:54,373 --> 00:27:55,432
I'll do it.

449
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:01,137
Well done, Dr. Kalu. Well done.

450
00:28:02,381 --> 00:28:03,440
So help you God?

451
00:28:03,715 --> 00:28:07,709
Yes. Dr. Melendez
can tell you...

452
00:28:07,819 --> 00:28:11,483
He has. But the fake
femur is yours, though, right?

453
00:28:11,557 --> 00:28:13,958
- How confident are you in its design?
- It's not fake.

454
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:15,153
Shaun, she needs to know...

455
00:28:15,227 --> 00:28:18,789
I know what she needs to know.
She needs to know will it work,

456
00:28:19,064 --> 00:28:21,192
she needs to know
how long it will last.

457
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,392
Yes.

458
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:25,727
Okay.

459
00:28:32,077 --> 00:28:33,340
He's his doctor?

460
00:28:33,412 --> 00:28:35,381
He is a surgical
resident. He's very gifted...

461
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,312
Is he going to
answer my questions?

462
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:39,878
Shaun, I really
need you to focus.

463
00:28:43,755 --> 00:28:46,224
- Marco is running out of time.
- Just let him answer!

464
00:28:46,325 --> 00:28:48,191
We already know the
answer. They don't know.

465
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:49,888
If this thing's never
been done before...

466
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:51,054
Be quiet!

467
00:28:59,171 --> 00:29:01,606
His toes are changing color.

468
00:29:09,281 --> 00:29:12,740
He's clotting. That's bad.
Page Dr. Melendez, stat.

469
00:29:16,088 --> 00:29:17,265
Murphy, what've we got?

470
00:29:17,289 --> 00:29:20,384
The shunt is clotting. It's
restricting blood flow. It's failing.

471
00:29:20,459 --> 00:29:23,361
We need a decision now. Are we
cutting off the leg or replacing the bone?

472
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:25,920
There's no doubt in my mind
that Marco's parents and fiancÃ©e

473
00:29:26,031 --> 00:29:28,023
all love Marco, but
it's become clear that...

474
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:29,932
Now. I need a decision now.

475
00:29:32,237 --> 00:29:35,639
His parents know him as their
child. Sonia knows him as a man.

476
00:29:36,141 --> 00:29:37,200
Replace the femur.

477
00:29:39,144 --> 00:29:40,271
Let's go.

478
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:43,779
Thank you! Thank you.

479
00:29:52,491 --> 00:29:55,222
- And there's the bleed. See it?
- Yes, sir.

480
00:29:55,294 --> 00:29:57,729
You ever clipped an
intracranial artery before?

481
00:29:58,730 --> 00:29:59,754
No, sir.

482
00:30:00,232 --> 00:30:01,325
Go for it.

483
00:30:08,907 --> 00:30:10,739
Just like every first time.

484
00:30:11,443 --> 00:30:14,345
You're a little excited,
a little nauseous.

485
00:30:15,347 --> 00:30:17,145
Hopefully, nobody gets hurt.

486
00:30:35,801 --> 00:30:37,041
Is it good to go?

