did you intubate her?

555
00:36:06,097 --> 00:36:07,121
Almost immediately.

556
00:36:08,099 --> 00:36:11,263
I did a sternal rub, she
had decerebrate posturing,

557
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:12,804
her left pupil was blown.

558
00:36:13,104 --> 00:36:16,871
I knew she had a subdural hematoma,
so I intubated and did the burr hole.

559
00:36:17,642 --> 00:36:19,634
She also had a flail chest.

560
00:36:20,512 --> 00:36:22,552
Did you check her breathing
after you intubated her?

561
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:23,639
Yes.

562
00:36:26,084 --> 00:36:28,815
At least I think I did.

563
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:32,923
Dr. Lim told me that,

564
00:36:33,558 --> 00:36:36,892
when Jenna came into the ER,
she wasn't ventilating properly.

565
00:36:36,995 --> 00:36:41,524
You inserted the tube too deep
into her right main stem bronchus

566
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,696
of her injured lung.

567
00:36:44,269 --> 00:36:45,828
We had no way of knowing

568
00:36:46,371 --> 00:36:49,864
how long she was hypoxic
before we gave her the EEG.

569
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:03,689
I drilled the perfect burr hole

570
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:07,084
into her skull on the side of a
road in the middle of the night,

571
00:37:07,425 --> 00:37:08,791
and I screw up her intubation?

572
00:37:09,694 --> 00:37:10,718
Yes.

573
00:37:10,862 --> 00:37:13,764
It was tough conditions
for anyone, resident or not.

574
00:37:13,865 --> 00:37:16,061
Any one of us could have
made the same mistake.

575
00:37:31,216 --> 00:37:33,981
I had a woman come
into the ER once.

576
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,548
A mother, 51 years old.

577
00:37:38,890 --> 00:37:42,657
Francine Parker.
She had two boys.

578
00:37:43,595 --> 00:37:48,431
She had a cough, a
bad one, but a cough.

579
00:37:50,001 --> 00:37:52,835
I checked her out, gave her
some antibiotics, sent her home.

580
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:55,805
Six hours later, she
was rolled into the ER.

581
00:37:56,741 --> 00:37:59,301
She had had a heart
attack and I missed it. And...

582
00:38:00,812 --> 00:38:01,836
She died.

583
00:38:05,150 --> 00:38:10,350
Not one day goes by
when I don't think about her.

584
00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:13,819
She was your first?

585
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:18,293
My fourth, actually.

586
00:38:20,832 --> 00:38:22,698
You're not gonna forget this.

587
00:38:23,835 --> 00:38:25,303
You never forget.

588
00:38:26,204 --> 00:38:30,005
But I don't know, maybe we're
better off for it the next time around.

589
00:38:31,776 --> 00:38:33,836
You gotta find a
way to keep going.

590
00:38:37,515 --> 00:38:38,539
Yeah.

591
00:38:39,517 --> 00:38:40,678
Go home, get some rest.

592
00:38:42,353 --> 00:38:44,686
- I haven't even told her yet.
- You're not going to.

593
00:38:46,624 --> 00:38:49,059
You made a mistake.
You're too close to this.

594
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,322
I'm not gonna allow
you to talk to the family,

595
00:38:51,396 --> 00:38:55,197
to anyone else outside
this hospital about this.

596
00:38:57,001 --> 00:38:58,299
Do we understand each other?

597
00:38:59,971 --> 00:39:00,995
Yes, sir.

598
00:39:06,678 --> 00:39:10,046
<i>I don't have all
the words to say</i>

599
00:39:13,084 --> 00:39:17,351
<i>I'm still healing
from my mistakes</i>

600
00:39:19,657 --> 00:39:23,822
<i>I'll take the weight if
it makes you stronger</i>

601
00:39:26,264 --> 00:39:30,258
<i>I don't want to leave
you in this place</i>

602
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,518
I called San Diego Community
Hospital to thank them

603
00:39:37,542 --> 00:39:38,874
for including us in their study.

604
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:40,673
They said they
were happy to do it,

605
00:39:41,379 --> 00:39:45,043
and they asked that I pass
along their thanks to you

606
00:39:45,116 --> 00:39:48,575
for your very generous
donation to their burn unit.

607
00:39:53,358 --> 00:39:56,795
I know you come from a wealthy
family, I don't begrudge that,

608
00:39:57,195 --> 00:40:00,927
but you can't open your wallet
every time a patient's in need.

609
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:05,236
The lines can get
real blurry, real fast.

610
00:40:08,072 --> 00:40:09,199
Yes, sir.

611
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:36,830
<i>Who am I to try and save you</i>

612
00:40:38,603 --> 00:40:42,233
<i>I ain't gonna hide
You have to fight...</i>

613
00:40:42,307 --> 00:40:43,570
What's this?

614
00:40:43,841 --> 00:40:45,002
My healthcare proxy.

615
00:40:45,743 --> 00:40:47,234
Jess, nothing's gonna happen.

616
00:40:47,645 --> 00:40:50,308
Really? That's good to know.

617
00:40:50,848 --> 00:40:54,080
<i>I won't let you down
I won't let you down</i>

618
00:40:54,152 --> 00:40:56,018
<i>No, no, no</i>

619
00:40:57,322 --> 00:41:00,520
<i>I won't let you down
I won't let you down</i>

620
00:41:00,625 --> 00:41:02,787
<i>No, no, no</i>

621
00:41:11,769 --> 00:41:13,829
Well, that was quite a night.

622
00:41:15,006 --> 00:41:16,770
Been a doctor for a long while.

623
00:41:16,841 --> 00:41:20,039
I don't remember a
night quite like that one.

624
00:41:21,212 --> 00:41:23,977
Why did Nurse Ferrara
ask if I wanted love?

625
00:41:24,182 --> 00:41:25,445
'Cause she's a nosy...

626
00:41:29,354 --> 00:41:31,016
Shaun, you really
don't want love?

627
00:41:32,056 --> 00:41:34,025
I loved Steve and my rabbit.

628
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:36,384
Not anymore.

629
00:41:37,195 --> 00:41:38,686
You don't love them anymore?

630
00:41:39,797 --> 00:41:41,561
No, I don't. They're dead.

631
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:44,533
You can't love
someone if they're dead.

632
00:41:46,537 --> 00:41:48,870
Well, I've lost people I love.

633
00:41:49,807 --> 00:41:52,504
I miss them. It hurts.
But I still love them.

634
00:41:59,017 --> 00:42:00,041
I don't want love.

635
00:42:05,390 --> 00:42:06,517
Okay.

636
00:42:10,194 --> 00:42:11,423
You want breakfast?

637
